// Basic Claude Desktop Configuration for SQL MCP Server
//
// SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
//
// 1. UPDATE THE PATH:
//    Replace "/absolute/path/to/sql-access" with your actual installation path:
//    
//    macOS/Linux examples:
//    - "/Users/yourname/sql-access/dist/index.js"
//    - "/home/yourname/sql-access/dist/index.js"
//    
//    Windows examples:
//    - "C:\\Users\\yourname\\sql-access\\dist\\index.js"
//    - "D:\\Projects\\sql-access\\dist\\index.js"
//
// 2. LOCATE CLAUDE DESKTOP CONFIG:
//    - macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
//    - Windows: %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json  
//    - Linux: ~/.config/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
//
// 3. COPY THIS CONFIGURATION:
//    cp examples/claude-integrations/claude-desktop/basic-config.json \
//       ~/Library/Application\ Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json
//
// 4. ENSURE PROJECT IS BUILT:
//    npm run build
//
// 5. VERIFY CONFIG.INI EXISTS:
//    Make sure you have a valid config.ini file in your project root
//
// 6. RESTART CLAUDE DESKTOP
//
// 7. TEST THE CONNECTION:
//    Ask Claude: "What databases do you have access to?"
//
// TROUBLESHOOTING:
// - If Claude doesn't see the server, check the file path
// - Ensure Node.js is in your system PATH
// - Verify config.ini exists and is valid
// - Check Claude Desktop application logs
// - Try absolute paths instead of relative paths
//
// SECURITY NOTE:
// This basic configuration runs the server with production settings.
// Make sure your config.ini uses SELECT-only mode for production databases.